<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

    <meta name="description" content="<%= @description || 'Connecting user-group organizers with the members of their community and the sponsors who help fund them.' %>">
    <meta name="author" content="https://plus.google.com/117224417942370890949">

    <!-- link rel="shortcut icon" href="" -->

    <%= yield :twitter_card %>

    <title><%= @page_title || 'User-Group List by UGtastic' %></title>

    <%= render 'layouts/google_analytics' %>

    <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', media: 'all' %>
    <script src="//maps.google.com/maps/api/js?v=3.13&amp;sensor=false&amp;libraries=geometry" type="text/javascript"></script>
    <script src='//google-maps-utility-library-v3.googlecode.com/svn/tags/markerclustererplus/2.0.14/src/markerclusterer_packed.js' type='text/javascript'></script>
    <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', controller_name %>
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>

    <!-- HTML5 Shim and Respond.js IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->
    <!-- WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file:// -->
    <!--[if lt IE 9]>
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/libs/html5shiv/3.7.0/html5shiv.js"></script>
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/libs/respond.js/1.4.2/respond.min.js"></script>
    <![endif]-->
    <%= yield :javascript -%>
    <%= yield :rss -%>
  </head>
  <body>


    <% if params[:version].blank? %>
      <%= render 'layouts/nav_bar' %>

      <div class="container">
        <ol class="breadcrumb">
          <li>
            <%= link_to root_path do %>
              <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-home"></span> Home
            <% end %>
          </li>
          <%= yield :breadcrumb %>
        </ol>
        <%= render partial: 'layouts/flash' %>
        <%= yield %>
      </div>

      <%= render 'layouts/footer' %>

    <% elsif params[:version] == 'alt1' %>

      <div class="navbar navbar-default navbar-fixed-top" role="navigation">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="navbar-header">
            <button type="button" class="navbar-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-target=".navbar-collapse">
              <span class="sr-only">Toggle navigation</span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            </button>
            <%= link_to 'User-Group List', root_path, class: 'navbar-brand' %>
          </div>

          <div class="collapse navbar-collapse">
            <ul class="nav navbar-nav">
              <li class="active"><%= link_to root_path do %><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-search"></span> Find <% end %></li>
              <li><%= link_to profiles_path do %> <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-bullhorn"></span> Build <% end %></li>
              <li><%= link_to profiles_path do %> <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-user"></span> Connect <% end %></li>
            </ul>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="container">


        <div class="jumbotron">
          <h1>User-Group List</h1>

          <p>Find, Build, and Connect with User-Group communities near you and around the world.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="well">
          <h2><strong>Find</strong> a community.</h2>
          <p>Join and follow communities near you. Share information and stay up to date on up coming meetings and group news.</p>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg active" role="button"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-search"></span> Find</a>
        </div>

        <div class="well">
          <h2><strong>Build</strong> up a community.</h2>
          <p>Promote your own User-Group and keep in touch with your community.</p>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg active" role="button"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-bullhorn"></span> Build</a>
        </div>

        <div class="well">
          <h2><strong>Connect</strong> with a community.</h2>
          <p>Promote your company or and connect with job seekers by supporting local User-Group communities. Build rapport with community leaders by supporting their communities and communicating through UGl.st.</p>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg active" role="button"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-user"></span> Connect</a>
        </div>

      </div>

    <% elsif params[:version] == 'alt2' %>

      <div class="container">

        <div class="jumbotron">
          <h1>Build. Participate. Support.</h1>

          <p>The three hardest things in running a User-Group are finding a location, promoting your community, and funding.
            User-Group List helps with promotion by letting you create a custom landing page to promote your User-Group
            community then with connecting your UG with sponsors who provide hosting, financial, or material support.</p>

          <p><%# = link_to 'Build your community today!', new_user_registration_path(plan: 'builder'), { class: 'btn btn-lg btn-success', role: 'button' } %></p>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-4">
            <h2>Builders</h2>

            <p><%= link_to raw('Build up your community presence &raquo;'), new_user_registration_path(plan: 'builder'), { class: 'btn btn-primary', style: 'width: 100%;', role: 'button' } %></p>

            <p>Start by building your landing page. You'll be able to list a description of your user-group, provide links
              back to your meeting pages and help people learn what your community is all about. After your page is approved
              and published you'll become eligible for sponsorship offers and promotions.</p>

          </div>

          <div class="col-lg-4">
            <h2>Participants</h2>

            <p><%= link_to raw('Find your community now &raquo;'), new_user_registration_path(plan: 'participant'), { class: 'btn btn-primary', style: 'width: 100%;', role: 'button' } %></p>

            <p>Never miss a community event again. Find User-Groups near you and subscribe for updates. Search to discover the
              community you might not even know existed!</p>

          </div>

          <div class="col-lg-4">
            <h2>Supporters</h2>
            <p><%= link_to raw('Register as a community supporter today &raquo;'), new_user_registration_path(plan: 'supporter'), { class: 'btn btn-primary', style: 'width: 100%;', role: 'button' } %></p>

            <p>Can your company host User-Group meetings? Register and add your location to our User-Group hosts registry.</p>

            <p>Register your company as a sponsor and we can help you set the terms and conditions for distributing your
              support to User-Groups near you or worldwide. We can help you find a worthy community where your sponsorship
              support will have the best ROI, both for you and the community you're supporting.</p>

          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Site footer -->
        <div class="footer">
          <p style="display: none;">&copy; UGtastic 2014</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    <% end %>

  </body>
</html>
